HEADWORD: Ternion
<hw>Ter"ni*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ternio</ets>, fr. <ets>terni</ets> three each. See <er>Tern</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>The number three; three things together; a
ternary.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
